CSS (Styling) Explanation
CSS is used to style your HTML elements. Hereâ€™s a detailed breakdown of how each block of CSS works:

1. General Body Styling
css
Copy
Edit
body {
  margin: 0;
  background: #0c0c0f;
  color: #00ffe1;
  font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
  line-height: 1.7;
}
margin: 0;: Removes default browser margins.

background: #0c0c0f;: Sets the background color of the body to a dark color, creating a "cyberpunk" feel.

color: #00ffe1;: The text color is set to a light cyan/teal color.

font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;: Sets the font to "Segoe UI" (a clean modern font), with a fallback to any sans-serif font.

line-height: 1.7;: Adjusts the line height for readability.

2. Header Styling
css
Copy
Edit
header {
  background: #121217;
  padding: 2rem;
  text-align: center;
  box-shadow: 0 0 25px #00ffff;
}
header h1 { font-size: 3rem; color: #ff00ff; margin: 0; }
header p { color: #99ffff; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
nav a { color: #00ffff; margin: 0 1rem; text-decoration: none; }
The header has a dark background and a neon-style shadow around it (box-shadow: 0 0 25px #00ffff;).

The <h1> is styled with a large font size (3rem) and a bright magenta color (#ff00ff).

The <p> below the title is a bit smaller and colored in a softer cyan.

The navigation links (nav a) are styled to be cyan and without any underline.

3. Container and Section Styling
css
Copy
Edit
.container {
  max-width: 960px;
  margin: 2rem auto;
  padding: 1rem;
}
section {
  background: #1a1a1f;
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
  padding: 1.5rem;
  border-radius: 8px;
  box-shadow: 0 0 15px #00ffcc;
}
The .container class ensures the content is centered with a max width of 960px and some padding inside.

Each section has a dark background, padding for space inside, and a border-radius for rounded corners. The box-shadow effect gives the sections a glowing, cyberpunk look.

4. Section Headers and Paragraphs
css
Copy
Edit
h2 { color: #ff00ff; border-bottom: 2px solid #00ffcc; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; }
.place h3 { color: #00ccff; }
.place p { color: #ccfdfc; text-align: justify; }
The section headings (<h2>) are styled with magenta color and a neon cyan border at the bottom to make them stand out.

The places' subheadings (.place h3) are colored in cyan, and paragraphs inside .place (.place p) have a soft cyan color with justified text.

5. Footer and Public Link
css
Copy
Edit
footer {
  text-align: center;
  padding: 1rem;
  background: #101012;
  color: #777;
}
.public-link { text-align: center; margin: 2rem 0; }
.public-link a { color: #00ffff; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline; }
The footer has a dark background and lighter text color for a clean, minimal look.

The .public-link class centers the link in the page and styles the link itself to stand out with a bright cyan color and underline.

